President Obama has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the 2014 Paralympic Winter Games in Sochi, Russia. The delegation will attend athletic events, meet with U.S. athletes, and attend the Opening Ceremony. The delegation will be led by Tammy Duckworth, a member of the United States House of Representatives. Other members of the delegation include Kathy Martinez, Assistant Secretary for Disability Employment Policy, Celeste A. Wallander, Special Assistant to the President, Anthony Robles, member of the President's Council on Fitness, Sports and Nutrition, Sandra Dukat, a Paralympian bronze medalist, and Brian Mosteller, Director of Oval Office Operations.